This paper is about inductive logic programming (ILP), which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) that focuses on learning logic programs from examples. The paper also discusses reduction techniques based on logical subsumption and entailment, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions SLD-resolution, which is a technique used in automated reasoning (cs.CR) and programming languages (cs.PL).
